reviews.text: Be nice or leave. Great sign staring back at you from the other side of the counter. And they are. Neat little diner on Broadway with a mixed menu. They have a great twist on the American classic with the Pizza Burger. Delicious. And the shakes are worth it on their own. Stop by this little joint that once was the stop for Seinfeld and company.

Like most others, we came here because of Seinfeld. Lovely little diner with traditional American comfort food. Grabbed some coffee and a slice of cherry pie, which was delicious. 
Staff were very friendly. 
Overall a great experience!
Cozy and simple diner to eat. A lot of variety on the menu at affordable prices. Also had a sweet waitress from Albania that gave us excellent service.

I didn't read the reviews before traveling all the way to this place but I was excited to see it. We went in and was sat at a table. Staff was very busy talking to each other and pretending to be playing basketball which was very strange. Place was sort of run down especially the bathroom. My boyfriend ordered the kabobs and asked about what the veggies were that came with it. We were told assorted veggies. He loves veggies well he got veggies from a can of mixed canned veggies. Really! $23 dollars for several pieces of meat tons of rice and tons of vegetables from a can. If we knew this we would have just ordered a burger. I ordered the parm and cheese sandwich it was just okay I only ate half of it. We were pretty disapppointed! We took a few pictures which was nice but wished we would have ate somewhere else and just maybe had a dessert here to see the place. Not what we hope it would be for the travel from Manhattan.
An experience, good wait staff.  Nice portions, fast and clean.  Enjoyed my visit and would go back next visit.
Great Ambiance. Really good food. Went for the breakfast buffet and they had a lot of good choices. They even have gluten free options as well.

Went for wedding reception. Things where good, not great. Table with bride, groom and wedding party served last. Seemed to serve one table at a time. When the head table was served, most others where finished. Adding one additional server may have helped.

I travel a great deal and I have had breakfast at my fair share of hotel restaurants,  I have to say that this one in particular was very good.  I would most definitely recommend this place for anyone staying at this hotel.
Excellent food and the prices reflect that, it is a little pricey but well worth it if you enjoy fine dining. The service is excellent as you would expect from an upscale restaurant.
Went for weekend breakfast; good variety--hot & cold,  unlimited coffee, etc.; Staff is friendly,.

Delicious food and excellent service! Tonight was our first experience eating Indian cuisine. Our waiter was knowledgeable and friendly with his recommendations and my husband and I both truly enjoyed our experiences.  We would recommend this restaurant to friends and family, and we will definitely be coming back ourselves.
This place was great. We ordered Lamb chops and chicken masala? (The first menu in curry categories) and they were nice. We will visit there again definitely.
The food is amazing and the wait staff so friendly. Every time we are in Ann Arbor we eat there as no other Indian restaurant is as good. We've been eating there for 20 years.

One of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at and I have been eating there for years. Reminds me of the nicer Indian restaurants in Great Brittan where I first tried Indian food. Authentic food served in a very nice atmosphere. The waiters are all very professional and efficient. I asked about a dish I used to order but was not on the menu now and the waiter said they would make it for me... Chicken Hyderabadi (not sure I spelled that right) delicious! I'll back when I'm in town again.

The food is delicious in every word possible! I went with my mom, and she's usually picky when it comes to food, but she absolutely loved their food. Our waiter was the best! The prices are not that bad. The service was good, a man in a suit (I believe the owner) came to our to check up on us. All in all, it was a great first experience.

I have been eating here since I was a kid (I'm 35). The deep-fried spring rolls are to die for. The owner and family are wonderful. Don't be fooled by the simple decor - the food is wonderful and from a first-generation Vietnamese Canadian who knows good food with classic techniques. Thanks for 25 years of fantastic dining!!!
The food: Fantastic. The service: Speedy and friendly. The portions: Huge. The price: Great. The wonderful free tea: The finishing touch to a perfect meal. Eat here. Full stop.
Food was great and cheap! They serve some nice tea as well with your meal. The staff was really friendly 😊!
I love his place! The food is always hot and fresh, the service friendly and the prices are more than reasonable. Would highly recommend!

Good service but very dirty restaurant and the most bland and basic pad Thai I've ever eaten, and I've eaten a lot of pad Thai!! I'd suggest eating elsewhere for both a cleaner environment and more flavour. There are lots of good Thai and Vietnamese restaurants in London. Thaifoon and Tamarine on Dundas are both amazing. Thai Cuisine on Gainsborough too.
